 Consider an individual with utility function 
\begin_inset Formula $U(x)=ln(x)$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is income.
 Suppose the individual rejects a 50-50 chance of losing £10 and winning
 £11 at an initial wealth level 
\begin_inset Formula $w$
\end_inset

.
